The '''Prince Edward Island Liquor Control Commission''' controls the purchase, distribution and sale of alcoholic beverages in the [[Canadian province]] of [[Prince Edward Island]]. [[As of 2006]], Gordon Coles is chairman of the Board of Commissioners and Wayne MacDougall is the chief executive officer.

The Commission operates nineteen retail [[liquor store]]s as well as a central warehouse and distribution center in [[Charlottetown]].

